REQ#1901:Informatica Adminstrator - Alexandria, VA

This person will be part of the team that supports a growing Data Warehousing and Business Intelligence environment using Informatica, Oracle 11g/10g RDBMS, and SQL Server 2005/2008. This individual will be responsible for the following:
‚Ä¢ Administering the Informatica environment on UNIX
‚Ä¢ Apply patches / upgrades / hotfixes for Informatica PowerCenter
‚Ä¢ Monitor performance, troubleshoot, and tune ETL processes
‚Ä¢ Will be responsible for 24x7 support
‚Ä¢ Work with Informatica vendor on any issues that arise
‚Ä¢ Support the Informatica developer team as needed

1. Ensure development teams are following appropriate standards
2. Promote and deploy Informatica code
3. Assist development team at design time ensuring code will run at scale
4. Serve as an Informatica Developer as needed to get work completed.
‚Ä¢ Write and maintain BASH shell scripts for administering the Informatica environment
‚Ä¢ Design and implement appropriate error handling procedures
‚Ä¢ Develop project, documentation, and ETL standards in conjunction with data architects
‚Ä¢ Work with other team members to ensure standards around monitoring and management of the Informatica environment within the context of existing enterprise monitoring solutions

Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ Excellent oral and written English communication skills

Specifically needs to be able to communicate well on phone calls
‚Ä¢ Must be able to thrive under pressure and have a strong sense of ownership and responsibility for the project
‚Ä¢ Minimum of 7-10 years of experience in the administration, architecture, design, and development of ETL programs using Informatica‚Äôs data integration tools;

1. Informatica experience must include working with large mission critical data systems (multiple terabytes in size with millions of rows processing per day)
2. Must be able to demonstrate mastery of Informatica command line utilities
3. Must be able to demonstrate mastery of quickly debugging and resolving issues that can arise with Informatica programs.
4. Must know how to navigate through the Informatica metadata repository
5. Expert knowledge of Informatica version 8.5 and above. Informatica version 9.x and above preferred;
6. Working with Informatica PowerExchange products is a plus
‚Ä¢ Minimum 2 full lifecycle project experience with small development groups, e.g., leading ground up development of Informatica standards in one or more previous projects.
‚Ä¢ Demonstrated ability to navigate through organizational and technical uncertainty
‚Ä¢ Mastery of Unix concepts and commands, including process management, scripting, directory structures, file permissions and editors
‚Ä¢ Solid background in Oracle database 11g

1. Must be able to read and understand an Oracle Explain Plan
2. Must understand and know Oracle hints
3. Solid experience building SQL queries, including creating sub-queries, minus/union, and inline queries
4. Stored procedure development experience
‚Ä¢ Fluency with business concepts related to relational and dimensional data models
‚Ä¢ BA/BS in computer science or equivalent experience
‚Ä¢ Experience with large scale database application like Exadata would be a plus

Strong organizational and time management skills.

Experience in implementing and supporting automation for managing Snowflake accounts, databases, and access roles.

Experience and understanding in proposing and implementing database and Snowflake query performance optimizations.

Experience with Git hub integration with snowflake and load data.

description:
Informatica MDM Developer
Baltimore, MD
Work Style: Hybrid (3 days on-site; 2 days work from home)
Looking for local resources. Resources from MD, VA and DC area candidates are preferred and will be given weightage.
Duties:
‚Ä¢ Informatica MDM Configuration: Configure and customize Informatica MDM to implement the Party Model, defining entity types, relationships, business rules, match and merge strategies, and user interfaces.
‚Ä¢ Data Modeling: Work with data architects and stakeholders to design and maintain the data model for party-related entities within the MDM system, ensuring data accuracy and consistency.
‚Ä¢ Data Integration: Integrate data from various source systems into Informatica MDM, performing data profiling, cleansing, and transformation to ensure data quality and integrity.
‚Ä¢ Match and Merge: Implement match and merge rules to identify and consolidate duplicate records within the party entities, enabling a single and accurate view of each entity.
‚Ä¢ Data Quality Management: Define and implement data quality rules and workflows within the MDM system to monitor, measure, and improve data quality across party [1] related data.
‚Ä¢ Data Governance: Ensure adherence to data governance principles and data security best practices during MDM implementation and data management processes.
‚Ä¢ Performance Optimization: Identify performance bottlenecks within the MDM system and optimize data loading, matching, and retrieval processes for efficient and seamless data operations.
‚Ä¢ Collaboration: Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including data architects, data analysts, and business users, to understand data requirements and deliver MDM solutions that meet business needs.
‚Ä¢ Testing and Validation: Conduct unit testing and integration testing to validate MDM configurations, ensuring accuracy and completeness of data within the MDM repository.
‚Ä¢ Documentation: Maintain comprehensive technical documentation, including design specifications, configuration guides, and troubleshooting manuals for the MDM implementation.
Education Qualification:
‚Ä¢ Bachelor's Degree from an accredited college or university with a major in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, Business, or other related scientific or technical discipline.
General Experience:
‚Ä¢ At least six (6) years of experience in MDM Development experience with a focus on Informatica MDM and Party Model implementation.
‚Ä¢ In-depth knowledge of Informatica MDM tools, including MDM Hub, Data Director, and ActiveVOS, and their functionalities for party entities.
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with data modeling principles and data integration techniques.
‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of data quality management and data governance practices within an MDM environment.
‚Ä¢ Proficiency in data profiling, data cleansing, and data transformation processes.
‚Ä¢ Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills to troubleshoot MDM-related issues.
‚Ä¢ Strong communication and collaboration skills to work effectively with cross [1] functional teams and stakeholders.
‚Ä¢ Prior experience with other MDM tools or cloud-based MDM solutions is advantageous.
‚Ä¢ Informatica MDM certifications, such as Informatica MDM Developer Specialist or Informatica MDM Administrator Specialist, are highly desirable.

description:
Informatica Data Engineer

Works with client management to identify and specify business requirements and processes for diverse development platforms, computing environments e.g., host based, distributed systems, client server, software, hardware, technologies and tools. Formulates logical statements of business problems and devises, tests and implements efficient, cost effective application program solutions e.g., codes and or reuses existing code through the use of program development software alternatives and or integrates purchased solutions. Works independently, receives minimal guidance. Acts as a resource for colleagues with less experience. Solves complex problems takes a new perspective using existing solutions.

Responsibilities:

‚Ä¢ Establishes IDQ environments (Dev, Staging & Test) according to project requirements
‚Ä¢ Design and develop data quality rules to evaluate and verify data transformations; update ETL scripts and data mappings to improve data migration activities using Informatica, Oracle, SQL, and other technologies.

BS degree with 4+ years in SQL experience and 5+ years overall hands on Informatica Data Quality (IDQ) development experience.

Strong understanding on Data Profiling / Data Analyst tool.

Skilled and experienced in Informatica ETL tool suite including PowerCenter designer, workflow, monitoring and repository services.

Proficient with Informatica ETL Integration using Teradata, Oracle, Mainframe, and SQL Server databases.

Understanding of reusability, parameterization, and workflow design concepts.

Performs technical walk-through as needed to communicate design/coded solution and to seek input from team members.

Strong Programing and SQL skills

Informatica Admin experience is a plus.

Excellent oral and written communication and interpersonal skills.

Strong organizational, multi-tasking, and time-management skills preferred.

Ability to work independently or within a team for problem resolution.

Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office tool set.

description:
Description

At CSpring, we believe infrastructure and insight go hand in hand. We‚Äôre looking for a seasoned Informatica ETL Developer to join our Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) team in support of a major healthcare data transformation initiative. This role is instrumental in building and maintaining robust data integration pipelines that ensure timely, trusted insights across Medicaid systems.

Whether you‚Äôre optimizing job schedules, scripting solutions in Teradata, or leading performance tuning efforts, you‚Äôll be working on meaningful projects that power decision-making and improve healthcare delivery for real people.

Why You‚Äôll Love Working Here
‚Ä¢ Build What Matters ‚Äì Play a key role in evolving data infrastructure that improves health outcomes across state Medicaid programs.
‚Ä¢ People-First Culture ‚Äì We prioritize your growth, your wellbeing, and your voice‚Äîbecause consulting is personal.
‚Ä¢ Technical Autonomy ‚Äì Own your craft while collaborating with a cross-functional team of analysts, architects, and policy experts.
‚Ä¢ Innovation with Integrity ‚Äì Solve complex problems while mentoring others and continuously improving system performance.
What You‚Äôll Do
‚Ä¢ Design, develop, and optimize ETL solutions using Informatica PowerCenter.
‚Ä¢ Implement automated data staging, integration, and scheduling processes across large datasets.
‚Ä¢ Build, test, and maintain mappings, mapplets, workflows, and sessions using advanced Informatica transformations.
‚Ä¢ Administer ETL environments (development and production), including backups, recovery, and system tuning.
‚Ä¢ Write and optimize complex SQL and Unix Shell scripts to support Teradata-based data marts and reporting layers.
‚Ä¢ Participate in solution design, requirements analysis, testing, and documentation activities.
‚Ä¢ Collaborate with cross-functional teams and clients to align solutions with business needs and timelines.
‚Ä¢ Provide technical guidance and mentorship to junior developers and analysts.
‚Ä¢ Keep up with new technologies and recommend improvements to enhance performance and scalability.

Requirements
‚Ä¢ 7+ years of experience in ETL development with Informatica PowerCenter
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of experience with Teradata (v17+) and tools such as Fastload, TPT, Multiload
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of experience in ETL environment administration (PowerCenter)
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of writing and tuning complex SQL queries
‚Ä¢ 2+ years of Unix Shell scripting (Bash/Korn)
‚Ä¢ Strong communication, documentation, and mentoring abilities
‚Ä¢ Bachelor‚Äôs or advanced degree in Computer Science, IT, Mathematics, or related field
‚Ä¢ Excellent organizational and time management skills

Preferred Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ Located near or within driving distance of Springfield, IL
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of data warehouse development experience
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of data modeling using ERWIN or similar tools
‚Ä¢ 2+ years of experience with Azure Data Factory and Snowflake
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with scripting languages like Python, R, or JavaScript/React
‚Ä¢ Experience with Informatica Data Quality (IDQ), Address Doctor, or Metadata Manager
‚Ä¢ Experience working in Agile environments
‚Ä¢ Exposure to Medicaid, Medicare, or healthcare data systems and standards

Location & Travel

This is a telecommute role with occasional travel (<15%) to Springfield, IL for client meetings.

At CSpring, we unlock the potential in people and data. If you‚Äôre a hands-on technologist who thrives in a fast-moving, impact-driven environment, we‚Äôd love to connect. Apply today to help shape the future of healthcare data infrastructure.

description:
Journey with us! Combine your career goals and sense of adventure by joining our exciting team of employees. Royal Caribbean Group is pleased to offer a competitive compensation and benefits package, and excellent career development opportunities, each offering unique ways to explore the world.

The Royal Caribbean Group‚Äôs Data Analytics and AI Team has an exciting career opportunity for a full time Senior Engineer, Informatica MDM reporting to the Director of Enterprise MDM & Quality.

This position will work on-site in Miramar, Florida.

Position Summary

We are seeking an experienced MDM Developer with a strong focus on Informatica SAS MDM and Party Model implementation. The ideal candidate will be responsible for configuring and customizing the MDM platform, ensuring data accuracy and consistency, integrating data from various sources, and optimizing performance. Proficiency in data quality management, data modeling, and effective communication with cross-functional teams is essential for this role.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities
‚Ä¢ Informatica SAS MDM Configuration: Configure and customize Informatica SAS MDM to implement the Party Model, defining entity types, relationships, business rules, match and merge strategies, and user interfaces.
‚Ä¢ Data Modelling: Work with data architects and stakeholders to design and maintain the data model for party-related entities within the Informatica SAS MDM platform, ensuring data accuracy and consistency.
‚Ä¢ Data Integration: Integrate data from various source systems into Informatica‚Äôs SAS MDM platform through IDMC, performing data profiling, cleansing, and transformation to ensure data quality and integrity.
‚Ä¢ Match and Merge: Implement match and merge rules to identify and consolidate duplicate records within the party entities, enabling a single and accurate view of each entity.
‚Ä¢ Configure Address Doctor Engine-reference and email and phone verification.
‚Ä¢ Data Quality Management: Define and implement data quality rules and workflows within the SAS MDM system to monitor, measure, and improve data quality across party related data.

description:
Senior Informatica Administrator

We are seeking an experienced and proficient Senior Informatica Administrator with over 7 years of expertise to join our dynamic IT team. As a key member responsible for managing our Informatica platform, you will play a crucial role in overseeing the installation, configuration, and optimization of Informatica environments. Your extensive experience in Informatica administration will be essential in ensuring the reliability, performance, and security of our data integration and ETL processes.

Responsibilities:
‚Ä¢ Installation and Configuration: Lead the installation and configuration of Informatica PowerCenter and related components, ensuring optimal performance and scalability.
‚Ä¢ Environment Management: Manage and maintain multiple Informatica environments, including development, testing, and production, to support the full software development lifecycle.
‚Ä¢ Performance Tuning: Implement performance tuning strategies to optimize Informatica workflows, mappings, and sessions for efficient ETL processing.
‚Ä¢ Security Management: Establish and enforce security policies and access controls within the Informatica environment, ensuring data integrity and compliance with organizational standards.
‚Ä¢ Monitoring and Troubleshooting: Monitor system performance, troubleshoot issues, and implement corrective actions to minimize downtime and enhance system reliability.
‚Ä¢ Backup and Recovery: Implement and manage backup and recovery strategies to safeguard Informatica metadata and configurations, ensuring data integrity in case of system failures.
‚Ä¢ Patch and Upgrade Management: Plan and execute Informatica software upgrades and apply patches to stay current with the latest features, security updates, and bug fixes.
‚Ä¢ Metadata Management: Oversee metadata management, ensuring consistency and accuracy of metadata across different environments.
‚Ä¢ Collaboration: Collaborate with development teams, database administrators, and other stakeholders to support data integration requirements and resolve dependencies.
‚Ä¢ Documentation: Maintain comprehensive documentation of Informatica configurations, processes, and procedures.

Requirements:
‚Ä¢ Bachelor//'s or Master//'s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.
‚Ä¢ Over 7 years of proven experience as an Informatica Administrator in a large-scale enterprise environment.
‚Ä¢ Expertise in installing, configuring, and administering Informatica PowerCenter, PowerExchange, and related tools.
‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of ETL concepts, data integration, and data warehousing.
‚Ä¢ Experience in performance tuning and optimizing Informatica workflows for large datasets.
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of security best practices for Informatica environments, including user access management and encryption.
‚Ä¢ Proficiency in monitoring tools for Informatica and experience in proactive issue identification and resolution.
‚Ä¢ Experience with Informatica upgrades, patches, and applying hotfixes.
‚Ä¢ Strong SQL and relational database skills.
‚Ä¢ Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in a team environment.

Dice is the leading career destination for tech experts at every stage of their careers. Our client, Accuro Group, is seeking the following. Apply via Dice today!

Greetings from Accuro Group !! I have an urgent opening for the project mentioned below.

Please let me know if you are comfortable with the requirements. Kindly share your resume @

Position: Informatica IICS Developer

Location: McLean, VA (onsite) (only nearby states)

Mandatory Skills:
‚Ä¢ Expertise in Informatica Cloud Services (AWS)
‚Ä¢ Expertise in Informatica Data Integration
‚Ä¢ Expertise in Informatica Application Integration
‚Ä¢ Expertise in SQL Queries
‚Ä¢ Well versed & hands-on experience with Kafka, Spark and Streaming in Informatica Cloud Services (AWS)

Job Description

Job Description: We are seeking a skilled and motivated Informatica IICS Developer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have expertise in Informatica Intelligent Cloud Services (IICS), with a strong background in Java, data integration, and messaging services. Familiarity with Kafka and Apache Spark is highly desirable. This role involves designing, developing, and implementing data integration solutions to support our business operations and analytics.

Key Responsibilities:
‚Ä¢ Design, develop, and implement data integration workflows and processes using Informatica IICS.
‚Ä¢ Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather and analyze business requirements for data integration and transformation.
‚Ä¢ Develop and maintain integrations between various systems using messaging services such as Kafka.
‚Ä¢ Write and optimize Java code to support custom data integration and transformation needs.
‚Ä¢ Work with large-scale data processing frameworks such as Apache Spark to enable efficient data handling.
‚Ä¢ Ensure data quality, accuracy, and consistency across systems and processes.
‚Ä¢ Monitor, troubleshoot, and optimize data integration workflows to ensure high performance and reliability.
‚Ä¢ Maintain proper documentation of data integration processes, workflows, and technical specifications.
‚Ä¢ Stay updated with the latest trends and best practices in data integration, messaging services, and cloud technologies.

Required Skills and Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ Hands-on experience with Informatica Intelligent Cloud Services (IICS), including Data Integration and Application Integration.
‚Ä¢ Proficiency in Java programming for data transformation and integration tasks.
‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of data integration concepts, ETL/ELT processes, and data mapping.
‚Ä¢ Experience with messaging services such as Apache Kafka for real-time data streaming and integration.
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of Apache Spark for distributed data processing and analytics.
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform) and their data services is a plus.
‚Ä¢ Solid understanding of relational databases, SQL, and NoSQL databases.
‚Ä¢ Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to troubleshoot data-related issues.
‚Ä¢ Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work effectively in a team environment.

Preferred Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ Experience with API development and integration using REST or SOAP.
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of DevOps practices and CI/CD pipelines for data integration workflows.
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with data governance and data security best practices.
‚Ä¢ Certification in Informatica IICS or related technologies is a plus.

Regards

Satyam Singh Bhardwaj| Sr. Technical Recruiter

Direct: +1-*165|

Email Id.-

Hangout ID:

Accuro Group

Raleigh, North Carolina

Project Name: Maryland Health Benefit Exchange Location: 750 East Pratt Street, 6th Floor, Baltimore, MD 21202The candidate may be required to work on-site or remotely on specific days as determined by client Interview Type: Phone/Video Interview or In-Person Duration of the Contract
Anticipated Start Date: July 14th 2025 Visa Requirements: At least 6 months of valid work authorization
(Citizen, H-1B, OPT-EAD, -EAD) Minimum US Experience: 4 Years of ExperienceDeadline July 5thRate: $50/hr on C2C Informatica Admin/Developer(Systems Analyst, Senior) Duties: Install, configure and manage Informatica Power Center. Assess the impact of upgrading Informatica and all its components (Informatica PowerCenter mappings, workflows, jobs, and other ETL processes). Identify and troubleshoot system outages, installation issues, and application code errors running Java applications in AWS. Generate and install security certificates and PGP keys. Work with the Control-M tool or equivalent to create and schedule batches and to create calendars and daily schedules for critical batches. Restore Informatica Power Center services and manage users and governance controls. Configure, maintain, and troubleshoot Redhat Jboss, Fuse, Apache, and Tomcat HTTP servers. Perform system troubleshooting by reading and deciphering app logs, and system logs from Splunk. Configure, deploy, verify, and troubleshoot SSL certificates. Read/understand/improve scripts related to the application, batches, and/or web services. Identify installation issues and application code errors running in JBoss/ Tomcat/ Informatica/ Control M. Provide options, recommendations, and additional actions related to resolving issues, mitigating risks, and resolving escalated items. Work with configuration management tool Jenkins to automate tasks such as code check-in software build. Manage, monitor, and configure the Splunk application monitoring tool. Support releases and adherence to change control standards. Perform scheduled maintenance activities such as patching, performance tuning, and backups. Execute daily batch scripts, days, evenings, weekends, and holidays as required. Perform capacity planning and scalability planning. Work with JIRA Service Desk to manage Incidents and Change Processes. Availability to work in rotation shifts mode. Adhere to all security, change control, and MHBE Project Management Office (PMO) policies, processes, and methodologies.Note: The candidate must be flexible to work overtime as needed, including weekends, holidays, and off-hours.Education: Bachelor's Degree from an accredited college or university with a major in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, Business, or other related scientific or technical discipline.Minimum Qualifications: A minimum of three (3) years performing day-to-day Informatica PowerCenter operations, functions, administration, or troubleshooting tasks. A minimum of three (3) years of experience as a Batch Operator using Control-M or equivalent. A minimum of two (2) years of experience working in a PostgreSQL DB or equivalent environment. Experience working in the health insurance marketplace, healthcare, or health and human services domains. Demonstrable analytical experience and ability to work in a complex system environment. Demonstrable experience with application and batch integration. Familiarity with Database and SQL functions. Ability to troubleshoot system issues by collaborating with a team of system operations professionals. Ability to work in a multidisciplinary team and effectively communicate with different functions.Preferred Qualifications: A minimum of five (5) years of experience supporting day-to-day operations functions of a complex enterprise system. A minimum of five (5) years of experience as a Batch Operator or equivalent, supporting day-to-day configurations and operations of various batch jobs in a complex enterprise system. A minimum of three (3) years of experience in identifying and troubleshooting system outages, installation issues, and application code running JBoss/Tomcat applications in AWS. Experience demonstrating critical thinking, providing options, recommendations, and additional actions relating to resolving issues, mitigating risks, and resolving escalated items in supporting a large or complex infrastructure/systems. Experience with operating, configuring, and troubleshooting Control-M or equivalent batch applications. Experience managing web-based systems hosted on the AWS platform. Working knowledge of Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) operations. Understand java runtime environment concepts such as heap memory, thread dumps, garbage collection, etc. Experience working with the Project Management Office (PMO) processes, policies, and procedures

We are looking for an enthusiastic self-starter who can meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment. The candidate will utilize best practices and will conform to client enterprise architecture, available products, and development methodologies.

At Yudrio we are seeking talented people that have an unparalleled ability to be their absolute best. We pride ourselves on our comprehensive rewards package including a choice of benefits, profit-sharing, and a low-cost vision and dental plan. This is a unique opportunity to help a small business grow that comes with tremendous benefits.

Yudrio, Inc. is a high-end Information Technology (IT) solutions provider. We provide deep expertise and capabilities of a large company while maintaining the intimacy of a small business. Yudrio has supported mission critical applications by providing innovative, customized, end-to-end services that demonstrate measurable benefits, increased efficiency, and reduced costs. Our results-oriented success curtails from our pioneering approach to solving complex problems. Yudrio offers services in the areas of strategy, application development, enterprise and technical infrastructure solutions. Yudrio has an impressive fifteen-year track record of delivering superior, dynamic technical systems to the federal government. Rate Range: $53/hour to $68/hour; The rate may be negotiable based on experience, education, geographic location, and other factors.

Informatica Developer job responsibilities include:
‚Ä¢ Design, develop, and maintain ETL workflows using Informatica PowerCenter and PowerExchange CDC tools to support data integration and transformation needs.
‚Ä¢ Develop and optimize big data solutions using PySpark, Apache Spark, and Python for high-performance data processing.
‚Ä¢ Work with SQL and NoSQL databases (e.g., DB2, PostgreSQL, Snowflake) to extract, transform, and load data efficiently.
‚Ä¢ Implement and manage data pipelines using workflow schedulers like Apache Airflow and cloud platforms such as AWS.

Desired Qualifications:

‚Ä¢ Strong hands-on expertise in Informatica PowerCenter, PySpark, Apache Spark, and data modeling with SQL/NoSQL databases.
‚Ä¢ Experience with AWS cloud-based data platforms, workflow schedulers like Airflow, and familiarity with DevOps practices and containerization tools such as Docker and Kubernetes.

If you are interested in this role, then please click APPLY NOW. For other opportunities available at Akkodis, or any questions, feel free to contact me at shashank.tewari@akkodisgroup.com

In addition, our associates may be eligible for paid leave including Paid Sick Leave or any other paid leave required by Federal, State, or local law, as well as Holiday pay where applicable.

Equal Opportunity Employer/Veterans/Disabled

To read our Candidate Privacy Information Statement, which explains how we will use your information, please navigate to https://www.akkodis.com/en/us/candidate-privacy-policy

‚Ä¢ San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance

description: Ace Technologies, a leading recruitment firm, is dedicated to sourcing exceptional talent for remote positions. Our focus spans various job domains, striving to connect top-tier professionals with our esteemed partners. Build Your Career at Informatica

We seek innovative thinkers who believe in the power of data to drive meaningful change. At Informatica, we welcome adventurous, work-from-anywhere minds eager to tackle the world's most complex challenges. Our employees are empowered to push their bold ideas forward, and we are united by a shared passion for using data to do the extraordinary for each other and the world.

Chief Architect ‚Äì North America

We are looking for a Chief Architect with experience in technical sales (Presales) and business strategy. You are a well-rounded technologist at heart with a functional background in Data Management. Location - New York, NY. You can work from home.

You will report to the Field CTO.

As a Chief Architect at Informatica, you will help work with the data management community, providing expertise, supporting strategic customer and partner engagements, and working with the product team in advocating for our Data Management Cloud (IDMC)

Technology You'll Use
‚Ä¢ 10+ years of data management consulting, implementation, or architecture experience
‚Ä¢ Broad range of experience with important cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP, Oracle, Snowflake, Data Bricks)

Your Role Responsibilities? Here's What You'll Do
‚Ä¢ You are equally comfortable working with executives and talking shop with technical audiences in both a business and technical context
‚Ä¢ You must share our passion and vision for making our customers and partners achieve successful outcomes
‚Ä¢ Provide pre-sales technical assistance and product education, share knowledge and best practices with peers
‚Ä¢ Collaboration skills for feedback to and cooperation with internal engineering

What We'd Like to See
‚Ä¢ Comfortable with both technical and executive audiences, whether impromptu on a whiteboard or using presentations and demos
‚Ä¢ Skills to act as a subject matter expert and trusted advisor to existing and potential customers and partners
‚Ä¢ Demonstrated expertise creating technical content
‚Ä¢ Engagement and influence with a broad audience including C-level and Architects.
‚Ä¢ Have conversations with executives and then map that to a very technical solutions and features for technical audiences
‚Ä¢ BA/BS or equivalent educational background, we will consider an equivalent combination of relevant education and experience
‚Ä¢ Minimum 15+ years of relevant professional experience

Perks & Benefits
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive health, vision, and wellness benefits (Paid parental leave, adoption benefits, life insurance, disability insurance and 401k plan or international pension/retirement plans
‚Ä¢ Flexible time-off policy and hybrid working practices
‚Ä¢ Equity opportunities and an employee stock purchase program (ESPP)
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive Mental Health and Employee Assistance Program (EAP) benefit

Our DATA values are our north star and we are passionate about building and delivering solutions that accelerate data innovations. At Informatica, our employees are our greatest competitive advantage. So, if your experience aligns but doesn't exactly match every qualification, apply anyway. You may be exactly who we need to fuel our future with innovative ideas and a thriving culture.

Informatica (NYSE: INFA), a leader in enterprise AI-powered cloud data management, brings data and AI to life by empowering businesses to realize the transformative power of their most critical assets. We pioneered the Informatica Intelligent Data Management Cloud‚Ñ¢ that manages data across any multi-cloud, hybrid system, democratizing data to advance business strategies. Customers in approximately 100 countries and more than 80 of the Fortune 100 rely on Informatica. www.informatica.com. Connect with LinkedIn, X, and Facebook. Informatica. Where data and AI come to life.‚Ñ¢

Build Your Career at Informatica

What You'll Do

Working remotely, you will sell complex technical products and services. "responsible for selling a limited number of complex technical products and/or services within a single product line" his includes a limited number of our products, typically technology or those that are strategic in nature. Specialize in a single product or product line, and carries an overlay quota. Generally not account-assigned; called into accounts as opportunities are identified and may work with account-assigned sales account managers to close sale. May manage the sales and technical team to support the sale of our products. This will include coordinating internal documentation that work with each Client.‚Ä¢ Manage the on-boarding process for new select Informatica Clients.‚Ä¢ At this level, incumbents will have subject matter expertise in selling our products and services, with expertise in their specialization.‚Ä¢ Assigned opportunities/engagements are typically the largest and of the most complex and strategic nature, where attributed expected revenue retirement would be among the highest of the sales specialist roles.‚Ä¢ Incumbents sell-to and work with the senior-most customer executive and CXO level decision makers.

Requirements

‚Ä¢ BA/BS or equivalent educational background.Familiar with overlay model

Perks & Benefits

‚Ä¢ Tuition reimbursement program to support your and personal growth

Our DATA values are our north star and we are passionate about building and delivering solutions that accelerate data innovations. You may be exactly who we need to fuel our future with innovative ideas and a thriving culture.

description:
Build Your Career at Informatica

We seek innovative thinkers who believe in the power of data to drive meaningful change. At Informatica, we welcome adventurous, work-from-anywhere minds eager to tackle the world‚Äôs most complex challenges. Our employees are empowered to push their bold ideas forward, and we are united by a shared passion for using data to do the extraordinary for each other and the world.

Expansion Sales Account Executive (Expansion SAE)

The Expansion SAEs will lead the upsell and cross-sell of enterprise software solutions from Cloud First Cloud-Native (CFCN) products to drive incremental subscription revenue from the existing customer install base. The Expansion SAE is expected to evangelize Informatica by generating additional revenue and business from existing customers to fuel our growth by strategically right sizing their existing purchases to meet their needs and expanding the departmental use case to an enterprise use case. This role nurtures and owns the expansion relationship within assigned accounts/territory and maximizes Informatica‚Äôs footprint within them for CFCN products. Incremental Sales revenue will be driven by customers‚Äô current consumption of CFCN products guided by the present adoption and their future expansion needs.

Nothing is more paramount to us in Informatica than customer success. In this role, the Expansion SAE won‚Äôt simply sell products. They are expected to analyze the consumption metrics, consult, and listen deeply to understand current and future business needs. This expansion sale to the existing customer base is backed by collaborative cross-functional teams. Incumbents effectively collaborate with other teams, including Subscription renewals reps, Sales Account Managers, Customer Success Managers, Customer Success Technologists, marketing, channel management, finance, and customer support, as well as external parties such as Alliances and Channel Partners. As its consumption-based expansion role, it needs a thorough understanding of Informatica platform technologies and/or SaaS consumption pricing. Prior enterprise sales experience within the SaaS ecosystem is a must-have experience. This is mainly a remote sale expand selling position where minimum travel to the customer‚Äôs location is expected based on customer needs. Travel is up to and may not exceed 10 to 20%, based on the needs of the business.

This role will report to the Chief Customer Officer organization through subscription renewals and expansion leadership.

ESSENTIAL DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES
‚Ä¢ This role is a quota-carrying expansion or incremental sales position.
‚Ä¢ Meet and exceed expansion sales goals (quotas) through analyzing consumption metrics, prospecting, qualifying, managing, and closing sales opportunities end to end within the assigned accounts/territory.
‚Ä¢ Expands sales within existing accounts while getting connected and building strategic relationships with key decision-makers.
‚Ä¢ At this level, incumbents will have expert-level knowledge of selling the company‚Äôs CFCN products and services.
‚Ä¢ Manage and track customer and transactional information in a Salesforce CPQ CRM system with high accuracy.
‚Ä¢ Provide regular and accurate reporting of pipeline and forecast through the CRM system.
‚Ä¢ Accountable for accurate forecasting, regular quarterly revenue delivery, and the implementation of agreed account-level expansion plans.
‚Ä¢ Provides customer feedback to internal stakeholders for product, systems, and process improvements.
‚Ä¢ Nurture and expand the company‚Äôs relationship with customer accounts of various sizes. As it‚Äôs a consumption-based sale, assigned accounts may be high in volume or larger and of the most complex nature. Hence assigned quota will vary.

KNOWLEDGE & SKILLS
‚Ä¢ Holds expert-level experience and uses professional concepts and company objectives to resolve complex issues in creative and effective ways.
‚Ä¢ Deep industry knowledge and understanding of a customer‚Äôs decision-making process, goals, strategies, and business objectives.
‚Ä¢ Expert-level presentation, financial/business acumen, and negotiation skills at all levels of customer engagement.
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of the enterprise cloud platforms, SaaS, PaaS, and SaaS contracts
‚Ä¢ Full functional knowledge of the deployment of software solutions and how consumption metrics drive expansion
‚Ä¢ Maintain an understanding of Informatica‚Äôs subscription and Consumption pricing models to provide customers assistance in the usage/use case-based expansion discussions.
‚Ä¢ Negotiate all facets of renewal contracts, Adoption, and consumption metrics to develop win/win negotiation strategies that maximize contract value while enhancing the customer relationship.
‚Ä¢ Complete, ‚Äúbig-picture‚Äù understanding of the business and technical contexts of key accounts to drive departmental use case sales to enterprise-wide expansion sales.
‚Ä¢ Fully adept at consultative effectiveness and establishing trust with internal and external customers.

EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE
‚Ä¢ 3+ years of field sales experience in the SaaS space.
‚Ä¢ Experience within data management software selling.
‚Ä¢ A clear track record of success in expanding SaaS subscriptions, demonstrated by overachievement of quota ($1M+ of ARR) and a very strong customer reference
‚Ä¢ BA/BS or equivalent educational background, we will consider an equivalent combination of relevant education and experience
‚Ä¢ Minimum 5+ years of relevant professional experience

Perks & Benefits
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive health, vision, and wellness benefits (Paid parental leave, adoption benefits, life insurance, disability insurance and 401k plan or international pension/retirement plans
‚Ä¢ Flexible time-off policy and hybrid working practices
‚Ä¢ Equity opportunities and an employee stock purchase program (ESPP)
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive Mental Health and Employee Assistance Program (EAP) benefit

Our DATA values are our north star and we are passionate about building and delivering solutions that accelerate data innovations. At Informatica, our employees are our greatest competitive advantage. So, if your experience aligns but doesn‚Äôt exactly match every qualification, apply anyway. You may be exactly who we need to fuel our future with innovative ideas and a thriving culture.

Informatica (NYSE: INFA), a leader in enterprise AI-powered cloud data management, brings data and AI to life by empowering businesses to realize the transformative power of their most critical assets. We pioneered the Informatica Intelligent Data Management Cloud‚Ñ¢ that manages data across any multi-cloud, hybrid system, democratizing data to advance business strategies. Customers in approximately 100 countries and more than 80 of the Fortune 100 rely on Informatica. www.informatica.com. Connect with LinkedIn, X, and Facebook. Informatica. Where data and AI come to life.‚Ñ¢

job_title: Informatica Consultant ** Largely Remote / W2 Only **
description:
About the position

The Informatica Consultant will play a crucial role in assisting with the UKG Pro Workforce Management project at a prominent Medical Center facility affiliated with a California Public Ivy university. This position is largely remote, but the consultant may be required to come onsite 1-3 times during the project duration to support the implementation of UKG. The consultant will work closely with the Human Resources and Payroll Departments to create necessary interfaces and ensure that existing functionalities are not adversely affected during the implementation process. The role involves advising the project team on risks and efficiencies, scheduling required procedures, and facilitating knowledge transfer. In this position, the consultant will guide and perform design, testing, and training as needed by the project team. The successful candidate will interface with key stakeholders and apply their technical proficiency across different stages of the project. Responsibilities include using Informatica PowerCenter to create mappings, transformations, and load data into target systems, as well as data modeling, building ETL processes, and performing data migration. The consultant will also be responsible for programming tasks using Informatica tools to address data issues, delivering work, and designing the work effort. Additionally, the consultant will proactively identify project issues and recommend viable solutions, provide training and support to the project team on interfaces and best practices, and develop and test interfaces and flat files. Close collaboration with Project Managers is essential to communicate and understand the goals required to complete tasks on time and within budget.

Responsibilities
‚Ä¢ Assist with the UKG Pro Workforce Management project.
,
‚Ä¢ Work with HR and Payroll to create necessary interfaces.
,
‚Ä¢ Ensure adherence to appropriate policies and procedures during implementation.
,
‚Ä¢ Advise the project team on risks and efficiencies.
,
‚Ä¢ Schedule required procedures and knowledge transfer.
,
‚Ä¢ Guide and perform design, testing, and training as needed.
,
‚Ä¢ Interface with key stakeholders throughout the project stages.
,
‚Ä¢ Use Informatica PowerCenter to create mappings, transformations, and load data.
,
‚Ä¢ Create data models, build ETL processes, and perform data migration.
,
‚Ä¢ Program using Informatica tools to update, test, and provide solutions for data issues.
,
‚Ä¢ Deliver work and design the work effort effectively.
,
‚Ä¢ Proactively identify project issues and recommend solutions.
,
‚Ä¢ Provide training and support on interfaces and best practices.
,
‚Ä¢ Develop and test interfaces and flat files.
,
‚Ä¢ Communicate with Project Managers to understand project goals.

Requirements
‚Ä¢ Experience with Informatica PowerCenter required.
,
‚Ä¢ Three years of progressively responsible experience with building integrations in Informatica.
,
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of working with hospital information systems.
,
‚Ä¢ Dell Boomi experience is a plus.
,
‚Ä¢ Experience with UKG Pro HR/WFM modules preferred.
,
‚Ä¢ Ability to evaluate requirements and recommend solutions.
,
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of functional and technical disciplines in a healthcare environment.

Nice-to-haves
‚Ä¢ Healthcare background is a plus.
,
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of PC applications (MS Office and MS Project).

Benefits
‚Ä¢ Opportunity to work with a fast-growing staffing and consulting firm.
,
‚Ä¢ Possibility of contract extensions after the initial 13 weeks.

description:
If you‚Äôre passionate about innovation and love working in an environment where you can constantly improve and adopt new technologies to drive business results, then Nationwide‚Äôs Information Technology team could be the place for you! At Nationwide¬Æ, ‚Äúon your side‚Äù goes beyond just words. Our customers are at the center of everything we do and we‚Äôre looking for associates who are passionate about delivering extraordinary care.

This role does not qualify for employer-sponsored work authorization. Nationwide does not participate in the Stem OPT Extension program.

This role will be filled in a hybrid capacity, with in-office collaboration in our Columbus, OH office 2 days per week.

Are you passionate about leveraging data to solve real business problems? Our team is looking for a collaborative, detail-oriented professional with strong experience in Oracle, SQL, and Teradata who can help us manage complex data needs and contribute to enterprise scale solutions.

As a Sr Engineer, Software Engineer you'll work hands-on with technologies like Informatica, Linux, and orchestration tools such as Universal Automation Center (UAC). A background in insurance, especially pricing and rating, is a bonus but not required.

Beyond technical expertise, we‚Äôre looking for someone who enjoys working closely with business partners, takes a methodical approach to problem solving, and is proactive in identifying potential roadblocks. You‚Äôll be communicating across multiple teams including analysts, engineers, testers, and both offshore and onshore stakeholders, so strong communication and documentation skills are key.

If you‚Äôre someone who thrives in a collaborative environment and enjoys making data make sense, we‚Äôd love to connect.

#LI-KR1

Job Description Summary
If you‚Äôre enthusiastic about delivering secure technology solutions to support a company providing extraordinary care to its customers, then Nationwide Technology is the place for you. Nationwide's industry-leading technology workforce embraces an agile work environment and a collaborative culture to deliver outstanding solutions and results. If that sounds like something you aspire to, we want to hear from you!

As a Senior Software Engineer, you will focus primarily on providing high quality, efficient technology solutions to business partners by crafting new software applications or modifying and/or supporting existing packaged or custom-built applications. In this capacity, you‚Äôll analyze, code, configure, test, debug, document and maintain applications.

Job Description

Key Responsibilities:
‚Ä¢ Analyzes, solutions, develops, tests, debugs, documents and deploys software according to standards and best practices.
‚Ä¢ Applies secure software and systems engineering practices throughout the delivery lifecycle to ensure our data and technology solutions are protected from threats and vulnerabilities.
‚Ä¢ Uses DevSecOps practices, tooling and techniques.
‚Ä¢ Drives continuous improvement and learning through ongoing training, practice and innovation.
‚Ä¢ Manages project priorities, deadlines and deliverables proactively.

May perform other responsibilities as assigned.

Reporting Relationships: Reports to a Technology Manager/Director.

Typical Skills and Experiences:

Education: Undergraduate studies in computer science, management information systems, or other related degree. Technology experience or non-traditional technology certificates can be substituted for an undergraduate degree.

Experience: Two or more years of analysis and technology experience.

Knowledge, Abilities and Skills: Proficiency in one or more programming language such as Java, C++, Python, JavaScript. Knowledge of software development lifecycle. Proven ability to tackle moderately sophisticated business and development problems. Ability to thrive in a team environment. Insurance/financial services industry knowledge a plus.

Other criteria, including leadership skills, competencies and experiences may take precedence.

Staffing exceptions to the above must be approved by the hiring manager‚Äôs leader and Human Resources Business Partner.

Values: Regularly and consistently demonstrates Nationwide Values.

Job Conditions:

Overtime Eligibility: Not Eligible (Exempt)

Working Conditions: Office environment may vary based on team and/or location. Associates may have on-call responsibility after normal working hours and/or on weekends.

ADA: The above statements cover what are generally believed to be principal and essential functions of this job. Specific circumstances may allow or require some people assigned to the job to perform a somewhat different combination of duties.

Benefits

We have an array of benefits to fit your needs, including: medical/dental/vision, life insurance, short and long term disability coverage, paid time off with newly hired associates receiving a minimum of 18 days paid time off each full calendar year pro-rated quarterly based on hire date, nine paid holidays, 8 hours of Lifetime paid time off, 8 hours of Unity Day paid time off, 401(k) with company match, company-paid pension plan, business casual attire, and more. To learn more about the benefits we offer, click here.

Nationwide is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive culture where everyone feels challenged, appreciated, respected and engaged. Nationwide prohibits discrimination and harassment and affords equal employment opportunities to employees and applicants without regard to any characteristic (or classification) protected by applicable law.

NOTE TO EMPLOYMENT AGENCIES:

We value the partnerships we have built with our preferred vendors. Nationwide does not accept unsolicited resumes from employment agencies. All resumes submitted by employment agencies directly to any Nationwide employee or hiring manager in any form without a signed Nationwide Client Services Agreement on file and search engagement for that position will be deemed unsolicited in nature. No fee will be paid in the event the candidate is subsequently hired as a result of the referral or through other means.

description:
Build Your Career at Informatica

We seek innovative thinkers who believe in the power of data to drive meaningful change. At Informatica, we welcome adventurous, work-from-anywhere minds eager to tackle the world's most complex challenges. Our employees are empowered to push their bold ideas forward, and we are united by a shared passion for using data to do the extraordinary for each other and the world.

Solution Architect - Remote

The solution architect role involves collaborating with internal teams, customers, and partners to create a comprehensive technical account plan/strategy and to lead sales engagements to their technical conclusion. As an important part of the sales team, you will drive success by understanding customer use cases and creating technical solutions using the Informatica Data Management Cloud. Your responsibilities extend to educating both customers and internal stakeholders about the Informatica value proposition, engaging in in-depth architectural discussions, and ensuring that solutions are optimized for successful deployment and usage in the cloud. Within the technical sales community, as a mentor to your team members, you will help develop collective selling assets, knowledge repositories, and enablement materials. To drive sustained revenue growth, you'll contribute to pipeline generation through the delivery of technical workshops, active participation in social media promotions, content creation for external distribution, and involvement in industry marketing events. Additionally, you will be a channel for feedback to the product management team and will support the Customer Success team through collaboration and supporting customer nurture activities to drive consumption.

You will report to the Manager, Technical Sales.

Our Ideal Candidate
‚Ä¢ Basic knowledge of top 3 cloud ecosystems and top 2 data related technologies
‚Ä¢ Basic knowledge of cloud computing security aspects
‚Ä¢ Basic certification on at least 1 cloude cosystem and 1 data related cloud technology at the level defined by the business area of focus
‚Ä¢ Skills on at least one INFA related software platform /technology
‚Ä¢ Engage and create relationships with influencers, coaches, and decision makers, and partners
‚Ä¢ Basic technical knowledge of hybrid deployment of software solutions, Data Warehousing, Database, and/or Business Intelligence software concepts and products.
‚Ä¢ 2+ years of relevant experience in data integration, master data management, or data governance
‚Ä¢ 2+ year of presales/technical sales, industry, or consulting experience
‚Ä¢ BA/BS or equivalent educational background is required.

What You'll be Doing
‚Ä¢ Manage customer engagements.
‚Ä¢ Share best practices, content, and tips and tricks within the primary responsibilities
‚Ä¢ Stay current on certification of services required for your responsibilities
‚Ä¢ Perform all activities leading up to the delivery of a customer demo with some assistance including discovery, technical qualification/fit, customer presentations, standard demos, and related customer-facing communication
‚Ä¢ Assist on RFP responses and/or POC's
‚Ä¢ Partner with the CSM team on nurture activities including technical advisory, workshops, etc.
‚Ä¢ Provide customer feedback on product gaps using Vivun
‚Ä¢ Support demos at marketing events.

Perks & Benefits
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive health, vision, and wellness benefits (Paid parental leave, adoption benefits, life insurance, disability insurance and 401k plan or international pension/retirement plans
‚Ä¢ Flexible time-off policy and hybrid working practices
‚Ä¢ Equity opportunities and an employee stock purchase program (ESPP)
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive Mental Health and Employee Assistance Program (EAP) benefit

Our DATA values are our north star and we are passionate about building and delivering solutions that accelerate data innovations. At Informatica, our employees are our greatest competitive advantage. So, if your experience aligns but doesn't exactly match every qualification, apply anyway. You may be exactly who we need to fuel our future with innovative ideas and a thriving culture.

Informatica (NYSE: INFA), a leader in enterprise AI-powered cloud data management, brings data and AI to life by empowering businesses to realize the transformative power of their most critical assets. We pioneered the Informatica Intelligent Data Management Cloud‚Ñ¢ that manages data across any multi-cloud, hybrid system, democratizing data to advance business strategies. Customers in approximately 100 countries and more than 80 of the Fortune 100 rely on Informatica. www.informatica.com. Connect with LinkedIn, X, and Facebook. Informatica. Where data and AI come to life.‚Ñ¢

description:
Role Description:

The Informatica Developer will be meeting with users, business units and data modeling teams to craft and assemble technical designs for solutions to be implemented. This person should come from a development background within large data warehousing environments and will be interacting with both technical and non-technical audiences within Informatica PowerCenter development teams while providing Production support and defining dataflows. The ideal person can take source to target mappings and be able to code independently.

Job Duties:
‚Ä¢ Work with upper management to understand the scope of the work and escalate to the right leads in case of issues/delays within large data warehousing environments.
‚Ä¢ Navigate UNIX scripts and create code as required and understand the business requirement or the downstream process requirements while serving as technical liaison between teams regarding new system implementations, development, integration, and changes while collaborating with management to design technical solution.
‚Ä¢ Design, code, configure, test, debug, and document system and application programs within Informatica PowerCenter solution implementation and support.
‚Ä¢ Review functional and technical specifications prepared by vendors.
‚Ä¢ Review test scope, test approach/strategies, manage defects closing during the SIT and UAT.
‚Ä¢ Serve as primary point of contact between users and engineering/development staff on nonproduction and production environments.
‚Ä¢ Ensure development guide and best practice for developing PowerCenter solutions are followed.
‚Ä¢ Support in Production for Informatica PowerCenter and fix production defects.

Education & Requirements:
‚Ä¢ Bachelor‚Äôs Degree is required
‚Ä¢ 4+ years‚Äô experience with Informatica PowerCenter development and related components technologies within large data warehouse environments
‚Ä¢ 4+ years‚Äô experience with UNIX OS
‚Ä¢ Experience with working on Oracle, SQL Server, PL/SQL and Informatica ETLs is required
‚Ä¢ Must have Advanced SQL skills & SQL Testing experience
‚Ä¢ Experience with Informatica Cloud (IICS or IDMC) is a must
‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of Control-M Scheduling, Datawarehouse architectural patterns, and batch processes is a must
‚Ä¢ Snowflake experience is required

Plus:
‚Ä¢ Hands on experience using Informatica MDM tool is highly desired but not required
‚Ä¢ Previous experience in banking/financial sectors is a plus

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: From $1.00 per hour

Benefits:
‚Ä¢ Health insurance
‚Ä¢ Paid time off

Compensation Package:
‚Ä¢ Yearly pay

Schedule:
‚Ä¢ 8 hour shift

Location:
‚Ä¢ United States (Required)

Work Location: Remote

job_title: Senior Application Developer (Candidates must have experience with Informatica)
description:
Company :
Highmark HealthJob Description :

JOB SUMMARY
‚Ä¢ **CANDIDATE MUST BE US Citizen, OnShore (due to contractual/access requirements)***

Seeking a skilled professional with hands-on experience in Informatica technologies. This role requires proficiency in Informatica IDMC, Informatica Saas MDM, Informatica CDI & CAI, Informatica REF360, and familiarity with on-premise Informatica tools such as IDQ, MDM, and PC.

Pittsburgh Location Requirement

If the candidate is within 50 miles of either the Pittsburgh or Camp Hill campuses then they are expected to be in the office on Tue/Wed/Thu ‚Äì otherwise they will be fully remote.

This job takes the lead in providing more complex application development services typically as part of a project team or in an application support role. Developers analyze, design, code, test and implement more complex systematic solutions to meet customer requirements that adhere to Highmark IT standards and policies. Developers provide general support to maintain more complex applications that meet the service levels, system availability, performance and quality levels required by their customers. May mentor less experienced team members.

ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES

‚Ä¢ Actively takes a leading role and participates on project teams in various project roles, including, but not limited to, Developer, Technical Lead and Project Manager, based upon level of experience.
‚Ä¢ Effectively communicates with team members, customers, partners and management, including assisting with or conducting more complex technical walkthroughs, reporting project status, enabling vendor solutions and providing accurate and concise documentation.

SKILLS

‚Ä¢ Experience with technology platforms, application development tools, business processes, software development life cycle used by Highmark enterprise

description:
Optum is a global organization that delivers care, aided by technology to help millions of people live healthier lives. The work you do with our team will directly improve health outcomes by connecting people with the care, pharmacy benefits, data and resources they need to feel their best. Here, you will find a culture guided by inclusion, talented peers, comprehensive benefits and career development opportunities. Come make an impact on the communities we serve as you help us advance health optimization on a global scale. Join us to start Caring. Connecting. Growing together.

We are seeking a highly experienced Informatica Extract Transform Load (ETL) Developer to join our Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) team. This role is responsible for being a lead in designing, developing, and maintaining robust ETL processes using Informatica PowerCenter and Teradata. The ideal candidate will have expert understanding of data integration, performance tuning, and data warehousing best practices, with a focus on supporting healthcare-related data systems. The selected candidate will lead a small team of developers from a project delivery perspective while being responsible for their own development.

You‚Äôll enjoy the flexibility to work remotely * from anywhere within the U.S. as you take on some tough challenges.

Primary Responsibilities:
‚Ä¢ Lead the design and implementation ETL solutions using Informatica PowerCenter to extract, transform, and load data from various agency sources
‚Ä¢ Automate data staging processes and optimize ETL job scheduling for performance and efficiency
‚Ä¢ Learn and grow in business understanding to support development of ETL solutions
‚Ä¢ Administer and support ETL environments, including development and production systems
‚Ä¢ Perform repository backups, recovery operations, and system maintenance
‚Ä¢ Oversee and lead the development of mappings, mapplets, sessions, and workflows using a wide range of Informatica transformations
‚Ä¢ Monitor and troubleshoot ETL jobs across development, testing, and production environments
‚Ä¢ Write and optimize complex SQL queries and Unix Shell scripts for data marts and interfaces in Teradata
‚Ä¢ Collaborate with stakeholders to define requirements, document technical solutions, and support project planning
‚Ä¢ Participate in unit, integration, and system testing
‚Ä¢ Provide technical support, mentoring, and guidance to team members
‚Ä¢ Communicate project status and deliverables to leadership and clients
‚Ä¢ Continuously learn and apply new technologies to enhance system performance and capabilities

You‚Äôll be rewarded and recognized for your performance in an environment that will challenge you and give you clear direction on what it takes to succeed in your role as well as provide development for other roles you may be interested in.

Required Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ 7+ years of experience with Informatica PowerCenter and ETL development
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of experience writing complex SQL and performance tuning
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of experience with Teradata (v17+), including Fastload, TPT, and Multiload utilities
‚Ä¢ 3+ years of experience leading the design and implementation of ETL solutions using Informatica PowerCenter
‚Ä¢ 3+ years of Informatica PowerCenter administration experience
‚Ä¢ 3+ years of Unix Shell (Bash/Korn) scripting experience
‚Ä¢ Proven solid communication, collaboration, and mentoring skills
‚Ä¢ Proven solid organizational and time management skills

Preferred Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of data warehouse development experience
‚Ä¢ 5+ years of data modeling experience using ERWIN or similar tools
‚Ä¢ 2+ years of experience with Azure Data Factory and Snowflake
‚Ä¢ Experience with scripting languages such as Python, R, or JavaScript (React)
‚Ä¢ Experience with Medicaid, Medicare, or healthcare data systems
‚Ä¢ Experience working in Agile environments
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of BI and data integration technologies across relational and multidimensional systems
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with Informatica Data Quality (IDQ), Address Doctor, and Metadata Manager
‚Ä¢ Residing in or near Springfield, IL
‚Ä¢ All employees working remotely will be required to adhere to UnitedHealth Group‚Äôs Telecommuter Policy

Pay is based on several factors including but not limited to local labor markets, education, work experience, certifications, etc. In addition to your salary, we offer benefits such as, a comprehensive benefits package, incentive and recognition programs, equity stock purchase and 401k contribution (all benefits are subject to eligibility requirements). No matter where or when you begin a career with us, you‚Äôll find a far-reaching choice of benefits and incentives. The salary for this role will range from $89,900 to $160,600 annually based on full-time employment. We comply with all minimum wage laws as applicable.

Application Deadline: This will be posted for a minimum of 2 business days or until a sufficient candidate pool has been collected. Job posting may come down early due to volume of applicants.

At UnitedHealth Group, our mission is to help people live healthier lives and make the health system work better for everyone. We believe everyone‚Äìof every race, gender, sexuality, age, location and income‚Äìdeserves the opportunity to live their healthiest life. Today, however, there are still far too many barriers to good health which are disproportionately experienced by people of color, historically marginalized groups and those with lower incomes. We are committed to mitigating our impact on the environment and enabling and delivering equitable care that addresses health disparities and improves health outcomes ‚Äî an enterprise priority reflected in our mission.

UnitedHealth Group is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer under applicable law and qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, national origin, religion, age, color, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability, or protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by local, state, or federal laws, rules, or regulations.

UnitedHealth Group is a drug - free workplace. Candidates are required to pass a drug test before beginning employment.

description: Ace Technologies, a leading recruitment firm, is dedicated to sourcing exceptional talent for remote positions. Our focus spans various job domains, striving to connect top-tier professionals with our esteemed partners. Leveraging a range of scientifically designed assessments, inspired by extensive research on high-performance indicators, we meticulously identify outstanding candidates.

About Us:

At Tech Mahindra (Tech Mahindra | Connected World, Connected Experiences), we live the philosophy of connected world and connected experiences. We thrive on change that is powered by the intelligent symphony of technology and humans designing meaningful and sustainable experiences. Consumer ‚Äòexperiences‚Äô are driving and disrupting industries like never before. Businesses must build seamless yet simple enterprises that collaborate, synergize, and drive the change. Change that connects us all and empowers us to deliver experiences that span across the digital, the physical, the convergent, and everything in between. That‚Äôs when truly connected experiences manifest.

Extraordinary is when experiences come together ‚Äì a continuous convergence of digital technologies, touchpoints, and most importantly people. It‚Äôs time to reimagine, reinvent, and revolutionize business models & operations as well as to transform enterprises into living, breathing, and connected businesses. We are the Digital Change makers who strive to change the way the world, communities, businesses, and humans interact digitally. We are harnessing the power of change, brought in by technologies, that makes it the most exciting time to be alive in the human history. Our universe, as we build it, disrupt it, and redesign it, is powering the digital change.

Tech Mahindra represents the connected world, offering innovative and customer-centric information technology experiences, enabling Enterprises, Associates, and the Society to Rise. It has 150,000+ professionals working for 1000+ Global Customers (including Fortune 500 companies) in 90 Countries. We‚Äôre part of the esteemed Mahindra group, headquartered in India. Under a new CEO, Tech Mahindra is committed to a transformative journey with 'Scale @ Speed' as our guiding principle.

Job Description:

We're looking to hire an Informatica Lead who has expertise in the following:
‚Ä¢ Experience in Informatica Master Data Management (MDM) applications based on identified architecture and support implementation of design by resolving complex technical issues faced by the IT project team during development, deployment, and support.
‚Ä¢ Provide production system operations and maintenance (O&M) support for end-users, applications, infrastructure, or network services. Troubleshoot existing information systems, application, middleware, or networks to identify errors or deficiencies.
‚Ä¢ Make recommendations and influence long-term technology strategy and planning for multiple business units.
‚Ä¢ Assist in the development and analysis of source selection strategies. Serve as a consultant and escalation point for issues.
‚Ä¢ Provide technical analyses to help define, assess, and monitor the technical aspects of the program/project or service.
‚Ä¢ Design innovative solutions using new technologies.
‚Ä¢ Recommend short-term alternatives when appropriate.
‚Ä¢ Work with vendors during the problem-resolution process as needed. Provides technical expertise across business functions. Identify opportunities to improve business processes via new technologies.

Technical/Functional Skills:
‚Ä¢ Informatica MDM Development
‚Ä¢ Architecting MDM Solutions
‚Ä¢ PL/SQL
‚Ä¢ Postgres SQL, Red shift and DynamoDB
‚Ä¢ AppDynamics and Kibana
‚Ä¢ Oracle DB
‚Ä¢ MDM HUB & SIF

Tools, Utilities &Methodology:

Service Now and Control-M. Service Oriented Modeling and Architecture, AGILE, Waterfall, Iterative, Object Oriented Analysis and Design.

Roles & Responsibilities :
‚Ä¢ To uniquely identify master data and its relationships across distributed data sources and deliver unified views of Member, Provider, Reference Data while dynamically synchronizing master data changes throughout the enterprise.
‚Ä¢ To mitigate the risk of data corruption across different interfaces by implementing one master data source, thus maintaining data consistency
‚Ä¢ Provides support Middleware team on the installations, code deployments, any configurations, any updates/patches that are needed, as well as any start/stops that are required on Stage and Production. In other words, any change needed for the infrastructure or code, the Middleware team will do.
‚Ä¢ Need to understand generic wrapper to call the existing oracle user exists by new java APIs( Java SIF).
‚Ä¢ To support real time integration custom java application. Execute the upgrades for Hub Server, Cleanse Server, Master ORS, CMX ORS and JRE and Implement Business Entity using Provisioning Tool.
‚Ä¢ Writing complex SQL queries on Databases.
‚Ä¢ Hands on experience on Match & Merge, Hub Store, Metadata Manager, SAM, Batch Viewer, Cleansing, Load & Publish process.
‚Ä¢ To interact with the customer in real time providing the best of data there by gaining best customer experience
‚Ä¢ Support Informatica MDM Batch Jobs: Ensure smooth operation of batch jobs in the production environment.
‚Ä¢ Enhancements: Implement minor enhancements to improve system functionality and bug fixes.
‚Ä¢ Tokenization Process: Monitor and support the tokenization process.
‚Ä¢ Data Management: Oversee the match and merge process for customer data. Identify old data and perform hard deletion of data using SIF mechanism
‚Ä¢ Health Checks: Perform daily health & daily status checks on batch outputs and updates to business stakeholders.
‚Ä¢ Understand Support applications on AWS Services, AWS Lambda or other AWS native orchestration tooling and maintaining DynamoDB, Lambda, and SNS services in AWS.
‚Ä¢ Deep understanding on application and log level monitoring tools like AppDynamics ,Grafana and EFK( Kibana)
‚Ä¢ ITIL Process( Incident,Change,Problem & Release management)

The pay range for this role is $135k - $140k per annum including any bonuses or variable pay. Tech Mahindra also offers benefits like medical, vision, dental, life, disability insurance and paid time off (including holidays, parental leave, and sick leave, as required by law). Ask our recruiters for more details on our Benefits package. The exact offer terms will depend on the skill level, educational qualifications, experience, and location of the candidate.

Tech Mahindra is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We promote and support a diverse workforce at all levels of the company. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, sex, age, national origin, or disability. All applicants will be evaluated solely on the basis of their ability, competence, and performance of the essential functions of their positions with or without reasonable accommodations. Reasonable accommodations also are available in the hiring process for applicants with disabilities. Candidates can request a reasonable accommodation by contacting the company ADA Coordinator at ADA_Accomodations@TechMahindra.com

Job Description:
We're looking to hire an Informatica Lead who has expertise in the following:
Experience in Informatica Master Data Management (MDM) applications based on identified architecture and support implementation of design by resolving complex technical issues faced by the IT project team during development, deployment, and support.
Provide production system operations and maintenance (O&M) support for end-users, applications, infrastructure, or network services. Troubleshoot existing information systems, application, middleware, or networks to identify errors or deficiencies.
Make recommendations and influence long-term technology strategy and planning for multiple business units.
Assist in the development and analysis of source selection strategies. Serve as a consultant and escalation point for issues.
Provide technical analyses to help define, assess, and monitor the technical aspects of the program/project or service.
Design innovative solutions using new technologies. 
Recommend short-term alternatives when appropriate.
Work with vendors during the problem-resolution process as needed. Provides technical expertise across business functions. Identify opportunities to improve business processes via new technologies.

Technical/Functional Skills:
Informatica MDM Development
Architecting MDM Solutions
PL/SQL
Postgres SQL, Red shift and DynamoDB
AppDynamics and Kibana
Oracle DB
MDM HUB & SIF

Tools, Utilities &Methodology:
Service Now and Control-M. Service Oriented Modeling and Architecture, AGILE, Waterfall, Iterative, Object Oriented Analysis and Design.

Roles & Responsibilities :
To uniquely identify master data and its relationships across distributed data sources and deliver unified views of Member, Provider, Reference Data while dynamically synchronizing master data changes throughout the enterprise.
To mitigate the risk of data corruption across different interfaces by implementing one master data source, thus maintaining data consistency
